content:
Add Chat to a Lightning console app so agents and supervisors can chat with customers.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED:
Customize Application

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026.

Before adding Chat to a Lightning console app, you need to enable Chat and create a basic implementation. You need to:

* Create a Lightning console app for service if you donâ€™t have one
* Have Omni-Channel set up along with a chat button or Embedded Service implementation using Omni-Channel routing

To add Chat to a Lightning console app:

1. From Setup in Lightning Experience, enter Apps and select App Manager.
2. Click Edit next to the console app.
3. Add the Omni-Channel utility if it's not already added.
4. Under Navigation Items, add Chat Transcripts.
5. Select the user profiles you want to add to this console under Assign to User Profiles.
6. Click Save and then Done.
title: Add Chat to Salesforce Console in Lightning Experience
